705	198	Intro to Clocks and Tricky Angles!	https://buet-edu-1.s3.amazonaws.com/auto_upload/bqB7NqnV8zd3nrQnYnLgZPaPuGZ2/1645973094717.png	t	easy	2	1645973127892	7	{"version":1,"description":"Let's take a more mathematical approach to angles in clocks. Previously, you should have faced 4 basic problems: Angles between the hour and minute hands of a clock when it is 12, 9 , 6 and 3 o'clock. In each case, the minutes hand was pointing exactly to \\"12\\"\\n\\nLet's think about the following scenario: will the angles between the hands be the same for 6 PM and 12:30 PM?\\n\\nFor 6PM, the hour hand points to \\"6\\" and the minutes hand to \\"12\\".\\n\\n![](https://buet-edu-1.s3.amazonaws.com/auto_upload/bqB7NqnV8zd3nrQnYnLgZPaPuGZ2/1645973094717.png)\\n\\nBut you might think that for 12:30 PM, the hour and minute hands are just reversed, ie the hour hand points to 12 and the minute hand to 6. If this were the case, the angle between them would be the same. \\n\\nBUT in reality, the hour hand moves a bit forward from 12. As you can see in the picture below:\\n\\n__* Insert Image *__  \\n\\nOur aim is to find out just how much it moves from 12. ","category":"clocks","lang":"en","interactiveType":"none","ansType":"mcq","type":"none","statement":"- Lets start by noticing that there are __12 \\"BIG\\"__ Divisions on a clock, __numbered from 1 to 12__\\n\\n__* Insert Image *__\\n\\n- __Each__ of these BIG divisions  have __5 small__ divisions, for a __total__ of 12 x 5 = __60 small divisions__ in the clock.\\n\\n__* Insert Image *__\\n\\n.\\n\\n- When the minute hand completes one full rotation, ie passes 60 of the small divisions, this means an hour or 60 minutes have passed.   \\n\\n- During this time, the hour hand completes its move from one big division to another, ie. *__the hour hand passes 5 small divisions in the time that the minute hand passes 60 small divisions.__*\\n\\n- We know, 1 full rotation = 360 degree = 60 small divisions.  \\nso, 1 small division = 360/60 = 6 degrees.\\n\\n\\n\\nIn our given example, of 12:30 PM, The minute hand is on \\"6\\" ie on the 6th BIG division.  \\n1 big division has 5 small divisions.  \\nSo, 6 big divisions have 6x5 = 30 small divisions.  That is, the minute hand has passed 30 small divisions starting from \\"12\\".\\n\\nnow, by unitary method,  \\nminute hand passes 60 small divisions-> hour hand passes 5 small divisions.  \\nminute hand passes 1 small divisions-> hour hand passes 5/60 small divisions. \\nminute hand passes 30 small divisions-> hour hand passes (5/60)x30 = __2.5__ small divisions.\\n\\nTherfore, the hour hand is 2.5 small divisions ahead of the Big division numbered \\"12\\"\\n\\nso, the minute hand is ahead of the hour hand by 30 - 2.5 = 27.5 small divisions. \\n\\nAgain, 1 small division = 6 degrees. so 27.5 small divisions = 27.5 x 6 = 165 degrees. So, the angle between hour and minute hands of a clock at 12:30PM is 165 degrees, which is less than 180 degrees at 6PM.\\n\\n__We note that depending on the position of the minute hand, the hour hand will move forward a bit from a big division.__\\n\\n__Click \\"YES\\" if you understood and want to move on to the next problem.__","explanation":"--","data":{"type":"mcq","data":{"options":["YES","NO"],"answer":"YES"}},"width":80}	ZqIeJnB1kt3ewWeJyL0N	bqB7NqnV8zd3nrQnYnLgZPaPuGZ2	t	f	\N	f
